1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 10=

3
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:40,620
It's all right.

4
00:01:40,770 --> 00:01:42,330
You've already done everything you can.

5
00:01:42,330 --> 00:01:44,660
I'll figure out the rest.

6
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:48,210
I'll head out first.

7
00:01:55,290 --> 00:01:56,260
Judge Shen,

8
00:01:56,410 --> 00:01:57,460
do you think Mr. Tao

9
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:59,410
might actually be secretly wealthy,

10
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:00,460
with some

11
00:02:00,460 --> 00:02:01,850
hidden treasures?

12
00:02:01,911 --> 00:02:03,180
There are quite a few antiques

13
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:04,660
in Ms. Liu's home.

14
00:02:05,210 --> 00:02:06,570
I don't know much about them,

15
00:02:06,770 --> 00:02:08,100
but what if, like me,

16
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,610
she doesn't recognize their true value?

17
00:02:11,010 --> 00:02:13,130
That might sound a bit rude,

18
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:14,410
but you get what I mean.

19
00:02:15,220 --> 00:02:16,730
I don't think so.

20
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:19,410
This is probably just an excuse
from the stepsons

21
00:02:19,690 --> 00:02:20,850
to avoid supporting her.

22
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:22,260
If Ms. Liu really had

23
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:23,690
the so-called heirloom

24
00:02:23,850 --> 00:02:25,290
or hidden savings,

25
00:02:25,622 --> 00:02:27,130
and she has no biological children,

26
00:02:27,570 --> 00:02:28,340
whatever she has

27
00:02:28,340 --> 00:02:29,890
would eventually belong to them anyway.

28
00:02:29,890 --> 00:02:30,890
They should be eager

29
00:02:30,890 --> 00:02:32,130
to show how filial they are.

30
00:02:32,244 --> 00:02:33,820
Why would they just disappear instead?

31
00:02:36,780 --> 00:02:37,690
It's a tough situation.

32
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:46,060
Come in.

33
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:48,340
Ms. Shu, you wanted to see me?

34
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:49,500
Have a seat.

35
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:52,340
You saw the system notification
just now, right?

36
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:54,780
I did.

37
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:57,100
Feng Shengli's case moved
to a collegial panel?

38
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:58,170
Exactly.

39
00:02:58,540 --> 00:03:00,850
The parties are fundamentally at odds.

40
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:02,290
Further mediation won't do much good.

41
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:03,570
Someone

42
00:03:03,570 --> 00:03:05,100
leaked this case onto the internet.

43
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,940
Mr. Ying is worried
about the backlash,

44
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:08,730
so he moved it to a collegial panel.

45
00:03:09,730 --> 00:03:10,500
Understood.

46
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:11,500
In the next few days,

47
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,540
I'll follow up on the mediation records.

48
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:14,380
If necessary,

49
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:16,260
I'll talk to both parties one more time.

50
00:03:18,290 --> 00:03:20,730
Regarding Ms. Liu's
filial support case,

51
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:22,780
I just received
the withdrawal application.

52
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:24,010
It seems Ms. Qin

53
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:25,380
still couldn't convince her.

54
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:27,730
I've actually been meaning
to discuss this with you.

55
00:03:28,450 --> 00:03:30,780
Even though
she's withdrawing the lawsuit,

56
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:32,410
it's clearly not what she wants.

57
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:34,410
If we approve it now,

58
00:03:34,410 --> 00:03:35,690
the underlying problem remains.

59
00:03:36,010 --> 00:03:38,730
She'll likely just end up
back in court later.

60
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:40,010
Exactly.

61
00:03:40,511 --> 00:03:41,980
That poor lady sacrificed everything

62
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:43,500
to raise those stepchildren.

63
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,540
And now they're

64
00:03:44,540 --> 00:03:46,380
forcing her to sign away her rights.

65
00:03:46,570 --> 00:03:48,500
It's a violation of public decency.

66
00:03:48,644 --> 00:03:50,170
We need to take this a step further.

67
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:50,755
I have an idea.

68
00:03:50,822 --> 00:03:52,690
I'll send someone to go
with you next Monday.

69
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:55,500
Mr. Tao is being buried tomorrow.

70
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:57,290
Ms. Liu has been desperate

71
00:03:57,290 --> 00:03:58,570
to get her husband's ashes back.

72
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,130
Things between her and the sons

73
00:04:00,130 --> 00:04:01,540
might get very tense tomorrow.

74
00:04:01,690 --> 00:04:02,500
I think

75
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,410
it's best if we go tomorrow instead.

76
00:04:05,170 --> 00:04:07,130
Very well. Better safe than sorry.

77
00:04:07,660 --> 00:04:09,380
It'll give her some extra support, too.

78
00:04:09,660 --> 00:04:10,690
However,

79
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:12,410
I'm cutting into your day off again.

80
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:14,610
It's okay. Just give me double pay.

81
00:04:15,890 --> 00:04:17,370
I can give you "emotional value,"

82
00:04:17,555 --> 00:04:18,822
but you're not getting a cent.

83
00:04:19,290 --> 00:04:21,700
I guess I'll have to
file for arbitration.

84
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:23,780
I'm off.

85
00:04:38,610 --> 00:04:39,980
Ms. Liu? Why are you out here?

86
00:04:41,780 --> 00:04:43,220
They won't let me in.

87
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:45,980
I'm afraid if I go in,
they'll only get angrier.

88
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:47,930
This is going way too far!

89
00:04:48,140 --> 00:04:49,900
Arguments over property are one thing,

90
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:50,900
but 30 years of marriage,

91
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:52,370
they won't even let her say goodbye?

92
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:53,900
Come with me, Ms. Liu.

93
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,290
They can't keep bullying you.

94
00:04:55,810 --> 00:04:56,700
Wait.

95
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,580
This is your right, Ms. Liu.

96
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:00,850
Don't let them scare you.

97
00:05:01,170 --> 00:05:02,020
Xianghui!

98
00:05:02,730 --> 00:05:03,930
Wait, hold on.

99
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:07,370
Ms. Qin is already over there
talking to them.

100
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,370
I have the family heirloom.

101
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:14,780
I'm setting the terms.

102
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:16,290
Listen.

103
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:18,100
This is my father's asset.

104
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:20,580
If you keep this up,
I'm calling the police.

105
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:21,540
Go ahead.

106
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,700
When they get here,
we'll split it all equally.

107
00:05:24,050 --> 00:05:25,140
As the widow, Ms. Liu

108
00:05:25,140 --> 00:05:26,250
is entitled to half.

109
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:29,410
You've got a shabby canvas bag

110
00:05:29,410 --> 00:05:30,900
with some sketchy box inside.

111
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:33,170
How do we know
there isn't just junk in there?

112
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:34,930
Take a good look.

113
00:05:36,410 --> 00:05:37,460
You call this junk?

114
00:05:37,930 --> 00:05:39,700
To Ms. Liu, this is a treasure.

115
00:05:39,755 --> 00:05:40,810
It's worth more than gold.

116
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:43,540
That belongs to our family.

117
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,250
I saw her sneaking around with it.

118
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,140
So you've seen it, right?

119
00:05:47,140 --> 00:05:49,140
Then let me repeat my client's demands.

120
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:50,540
Ms. Liu

121
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:52,290
has ordered today's burial canceled.

122
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:54,580
She will take Mr. Tao's ashes

123
00:05:54,580 --> 00:05:55,540
and bury him elsewhere.

124
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:57,290
Don't you worry.

125
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:59,050
She won't ask for a cent in support,

126
00:05:59,290 --> 00:06:01,170
nor will she claim the property
or his effects.

127
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:05,220
Fine.

128
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:07,290
Let us check the box.

129
00:06:07,290 --> 00:06:09,490
We need to see
what this "treasure" is worth.

130
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:11,980
You don't believe me?

131
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:13,490
Suit yourselves.

132
00:06:13,490 --> 00:06:14,900
I'll just advise my client

133
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:17,140
to take these treasures back
for her retirement.

134
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,460
Your father is gone anyway.

135
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:19,580
Giving up an inheritance

136
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:20,460
for some ashes...

137
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,780
It's honestly not worth it.

138
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:24,244
- Hand it over before you leave!
- What are you doing?!

139
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:24,930
Get out of the way.

140
00:06:24,930 --> 00:06:26,410
- Give it here right now!
- I'm calling for help!

141
00:06:26,410 --> 00:06:27,540
- This belongs to us!
- Help!

142
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:29,850
Help! Someone help me!

143
00:06:30,050 --> 00:06:30,930
What's going on?

144
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:31,930
Let go.

145
00:06:31,930 --> 00:06:32,730
Judge Shen!

146
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:34,290
Back off.

147
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:35,290
What happened?

148
00:06:36,490 --> 00:06:37,100
Judge Shen!

149
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:37,660
A misunderstanding.

150
00:06:37,660 --> 00:06:38,660
They were getting violent.

151
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:39,930
Please, do something.

152
00:06:40,170 --> 00:06:41,100
What's the situation?

153
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:41,580
I...

154
00:06:41,580 --> 00:06:42,540
I came

155
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:44,410
to negotiate for my client.

156
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:46,290
We agreed to trade this family heirloom

157
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:48,170
for Mr. Tao's ashes.

158
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:49,700
They refused,

159
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,980
but then they tried to rob me.

160
00:06:51,980 --> 00:06:54,410
No, no! It's a misunderstanding!

161
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:56,700
The family heirloom?

162
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:57,810
Yes.

163
00:06:59,020 --> 00:06:59,780
That day,

164
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:01,050
I opened it and saw it

165
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:02,460
at Ms. Liu's house.

166
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:03,850
Your colleague was there, too.

167
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:05,220
Don't you remember?

168
00:07:05,810 --> 00:07:07,020
Right? That item is

169
00:07:07,020 --> 00:07:08,170
incredibly precious

170
00:07:08,170 --> 00:07:09,370
to Ms. Liu, isn't it?

171
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:10,810
Yes, that's right.

172
00:07:10,810 --> 00:07:12,050
I know. I've seen it.

173
00:07:12,610 --> 00:07:13,780
Now, Ms. Liu

174
00:07:13,930 --> 00:07:15,980
is willing to give up these treasures

175
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:17,930
just to get Mr. Tao's ashes back.

176
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:19,160
As her authorized representative,

177
00:07:19,177 --> 00:07:20,540
I was strongly against this move.

178
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:21,490
I believe the law

179
00:07:21,490 --> 00:07:22,810
would definitely be on our side

180
00:07:22,810 --> 00:07:25,700
and grant Ms. Liu a win on all counts.

181
00:07:26,170 --> 00:07:26,810
Besides,

182
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:28,850
marital assets
should be split fifty-fifty.

183
00:07:28,850 --> 00:07:30,850
The rest is then divided
among the three of you.

184
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:31,540
Also, Ms. Liu

185
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:33,290
took care of Mr. Tao the most.

186
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:34,700
She's entitled to the greatest share.

187
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:35,780
Right, Judge Shen?

188
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:40,170
Well, I'm not in a position to comment.

189
00:07:40,490 --> 00:07:41,610
I came here today

190
00:07:41,610 --> 00:07:42,610
to understand

191
00:07:42,610 --> 00:07:44,050
Ms. Liu's true intentions.

192
00:07:44,610 --> 00:07:45,490
Was her withdrawal

193
00:07:45,490 --> 00:07:47,140
made under any form of duress?

194
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:48,540
No, not at all,

195
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:49,370
Judge Shen.

196
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:51,290
Between our stepmother and us,

197
00:07:51,355 --> 00:07:52,610
it was just a misunderstanding.

198
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,850
She's lived with us for thirty years.

199
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:55,540
All this time,

200
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:57,810
we've always gotten along perfectly.

201
00:07:58,290 --> 00:07:59,290
We're a family.

202
00:07:59,290 --> 00:08:01,050
Any misunderstanding can be resolved.

203
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:02,930
She just thought it through

204
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:04,490
and realized she was in the wrong.

205
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:05,610
Look,

206
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:07,460
since Judge Shen is here,

207
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:09,100
please help us witness this.

208
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:10,220
In a bit,

209
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:11,020
let my stepmother

210
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:13,020
go to the hall
to collect my father's ashes.

211
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,410
We'll have a farewell ceremony too.

212
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:17,140
Ultimately, the ashes

213
00:08:17,290 --> 00:08:18,340
should obviously

214
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:18,930
be placed

215
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,580
with the partner who loved him

216
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:21,540
all her life.

217
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:22,290
Right, Brother?

218
00:08:22,490 --> 00:08:23,250
As for

219
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:25,170
the things my father left behind,

220
00:08:25,810 --> 00:08:27,850
my stepmother hasn't
handled money in her life,

221
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:29,250
let alone financial management.

222
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:31,170
The two of us

223
00:08:31,170 --> 00:08:33,490
are just worried she'll get scammed.

224
00:08:33,490 --> 00:08:35,770
We don't want
her retirement fund to vanish.

225
00:08:35,770 --> 00:08:36,130
Right.

226
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:37,010
So,

227
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:38,250
please be our witness

228
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:40,100
with the handling of the box.

229
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,130
Once the ceremony is done,

230
00:08:41,370 --> 00:08:42,820
give it to us for safekeeping.

231
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:44,060
Exactly.

232
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,010
Clerk Chen,

233
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:51,770
is this procedure compliant?

234
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,770
Since it's a voluntary agreement,

235
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:55,370
we can just act as witnesses.

236
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:56,490
If you're worried,

237
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,010
I'll record the whole thing.

238
00:08:58,010 --> 00:08:59,530
Yes, record it.

239
00:09:01,610 --> 00:09:02,630
Counsel for the plaintiff,

240
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:04,420
do you agree?

241
00:09:06,820 --> 00:09:07,730
I agree.

242
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:11,820
Fine.

243
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:12,850
It's settled then.

244
00:09:58,490 --> 00:09:59,700
I can finally

245
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,300
take you home now.

246
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,700
What about the box?

247
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:29,460
Just wait a moment.

248
00:10:29,460 --> 00:10:31,100
I'll explain once I've seen Ms. Liu off.

249
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:34,850
Give me the bag.

250
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:39,700
Ms. Liu,

251
00:10:39,940 --> 00:10:41,250
I've put your things in the car.

252
00:10:41,770 --> 00:10:43,180
You may head to the airport now.

253
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:46,220
Thank you, Ms. Qin.

254
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:49,420
Thank you, Judge Shen.

255
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,100
Take care of yourself, Ms. Liu.

256
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,300
My husband and I

257
00:10:55,130 --> 00:10:56,730
will be forever grateful to you both.

258
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,610
Please, take good care of yourself.

259
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:13,580
Drive safely, Sir.

260
00:11:15,420 --> 00:11:16,420
Thank you.

261
00:11:30,250 --> 00:11:31,100
Judge Shen,

262
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:32,530
give them the items.

263
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:43,700
What is this?

264
00:11:45,460 --> 00:11:47,060
Where's the stuff inside?

265
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:49,180
Judge Shen!

266
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:51,130
Look at this garbage!

267
00:11:51,130 --> 00:11:53,180
She said right in front of you

268
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:55,220
that this was worth more than gold!

269
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:56,770
She must have swapped it out!

270
00:11:56,770 --> 00:11:57,490
Exactly!

271
00:11:57,490 --> 00:11:58,650
I didn't lie to you.

272
00:11:58,650 --> 00:12:00,700
These are Ms. Liu's treasures.

273
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,340
Cut the nonsense!

274
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:03,850
I only care about what you told us.

275
00:12:03,980 --> 00:12:05,250
You swapped it!

276
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,610
"Worth more than gold," my foot!

277
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:08,820
How much are you going to pay us back?

278
00:12:09,820 --> 00:12:11,370
This is Ms. Liu's treasure.

279
00:12:11,890 --> 00:12:13,700
I saw it myself at your parents' house.

280
00:12:14,580 --> 00:12:15,850
Ms. Qin didn't swap anything.

281
00:12:17,822 --> 00:12:18,650
That's impossible.

282
00:12:18,650 --> 00:12:20,010
There must be something else.

283
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,580
Take a good look at what's in there.

284
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:24,490
They're labeled
with your names and ages.

285
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:27,010
These are the baby teeth
you both lost as kids.

286
00:12:33,460 --> 00:12:35,490
Ms. Liu raised you like her own.

287
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:38,530
Every time one of you lost a tooth,

288
00:12:38,890 --> 00:12:40,490
she collected it

289
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:42,340
and kept it like precious jewels.

290
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,420
The memories of raising you

291
00:12:44,420 --> 00:12:45,650
were actually

292
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:47,340
her most valuable treasure.

293
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:50,180
Ms. Liu always treated you

294
00:12:50,180 --> 00:12:51,530
like her own children.

295
00:12:52,088 --> 00:12:53,730
She never imagined
that once you grew up,

296
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:54,980
you'd refuse to care for her

297
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,466
and fight her over an inheritance.

298
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:00,220
These things

299
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:03,180
were once so dear to her.

300
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:07,220
She doesn't want them anymore.

301
00:13:12,770 --> 00:13:14,650
(The law is a sturdy shield,)

302
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:17,300
(guarding the tangible wealth.)

303
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:20,100
(But the truly priceless treasure)

304
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,220
(often exist beyond
the scales and the gavel,)

305
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:24,130
(in a realm
where no judgment can reach.)

306
00:13:24,488 --> 00:13:26,300
(You thought
what she clutched in her hands)

307
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:27,730
(was gold and silver.)

308
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:29,700
(Yet you never knew
that deep in that box,)

309
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:31,288
(what she cherished as life itself)

310
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:33,300
(were the teeth)

311
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,460
(you cast aside like trash.)

312
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,300
(Every baby tooth)

313
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:39,850
(was a memory of growing up,)

314
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:42,460
(recording a time
that can never be replaced.)

315
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:45,010
(They held the devotion of a mother.)

316
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,490
(Perhaps not of your own blood,)

317
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:48,420
(but she poured her soul)

318
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:51,420
(into her every dream
and safeguarding of this home.)

319
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:52,850
(And now,)

320
00:13:53,180 --> 00:13:55,180
(when the bond of affection
has been severed,)

321
00:13:55,770 --> 00:13:58,340
(she can choose to let go
of this heavy memory.)

322
00:13:59,010 --> 00:14:01,460
(But can she finish
the rest of her journey)

323
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:03,370
(with peace and dignity?)

324
00:14:03,730 --> 00:14:05,730
(The verdict the law cannot reach)

325
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:08,610
(must be left to conscience and time.)

326
00:14:09,622 --> 00:14:10,940
(I wonder if those children,)

327
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:13,010
(who so easily cut these bonds,)

328
00:14:13,530 --> 00:14:16,490
(can withstand
the gaze of that box of teeth.)

329
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:19,066
(I wonder if their hearts
will feel even a flicker)

330
00:14:19,088 --> 00:14:20,340
(of true regret or guilt.)

331
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:23,420
(Will they only mourn
the treasure they didn't get,)

332
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,100
(or will they finally realize)

333
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:28,370
(just how precious
was the love they lost?)

334
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:29,380
(Lian Mutton Soup)

335
00:14:30,890 --> 00:14:32,420
Soup's here!

336
00:14:33,511 --> 00:14:34,490
Watch out. It's hot.

337
00:14:34,490 --> 00:14:35,820
Welcome! Please, come on in.

338
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:37,700
Here's your mutton soup.

339
00:14:38,610 --> 00:14:39,580
Yongjiu!

340
00:14:41,890 --> 00:14:43,890
Shen! You're a rare sight!

341
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:45,060
Hello, Senior.

342
00:14:45,060 --> 00:14:47,300
We didn't cross paths
much in the criminal division,

343
00:14:47,460 --> 00:14:49,490
but I've heard plenty
of your legendary stories.

344
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,420
That's all ancient history.

345
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:52,650
A closed chapter. Let it go.

346
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,340
They're all upstairs.

347
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:55,530
Come on, this way.

348
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:03,820
Let me get you some more.

349
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:04,890
Thanks.

350
00:15:06,850 --> 00:15:08,130
Slow down.

351
00:15:08,130 --> 00:15:09,850
Ms. He, Ms. Shu, that's enough.

352
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:11,890
Shu Jing.

353
00:15:12,490 --> 00:15:13,940
Shu Jing.

354
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:15,100
Look who's here.

355
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:15,890
Judge Shen!

356
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:17,300
- Judge Shen!
- Judge Shen!

357
00:15:18,060 --> 00:15:19,490
Why so shocked?

358
00:15:19,490 --> 00:15:21,010
You mentioned dinner in the group chat.

359
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:23,130
I guess I should've given a heads-up.

360
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,130
Well, yeah.

361
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:25,130
We tagged you ten times,

362
00:15:25,130 --> 00:15:26,622
and you ignored us every single time.

363
00:15:26,711 --> 00:15:27,730
I was actually thinking

364
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:28,530
I'll just

365
00:15:28,530 --> 00:15:30,340
eat your portion for you.

366
00:15:30,490 --> 00:15:31,980
And now, you appeared out of nowhere.

367
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,010
My heart

368
00:15:33,580 --> 00:15:34,610
just sank.

369
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:37,700
What are you doing here?

370
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,530
Isn't this a Family Court dinner?

371
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:41,130
Why is an outsider hanging around?

372
00:15:41,222 --> 00:15:42,460
Who are you calling an outsider?

373
00:15:42,460 --> 00:15:43,980
Mr. Lian is my mentor.

374
00:15:44,370 --> 00:15:46,300
Why are you already picking on me?

375
00:15:46,511 --> 00:15:47,730
Let me tell you something.

376
00:15:47,730 --> 00:15:49,730
I've got way
more seniority here than you.

377
00:15:50,010 --> 00:15:50,940
The AC,

378
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:52,300
the tables, chairs, pots, and pans,

379
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:53,730
even the sauce dishes recognize me.

380
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:55,890
And you, a rookie,
want to argue with me?

381
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:57,890
Alright, alright, that's enough.

382
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,250
You're the most senior. Happy?

383
00:15:59,866 --> 00:16:01,370
Look. There are so many of us today.

384
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:02,530
How about we open another table?

385
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:03,377
- Sound good?
- Yeah.

386
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:03,890
Come on, then.

387
00:16:03,890 --> 00:16:05,420
Everyone, this way. Let's go.

388
00:16:05,822 --> 00:16:06,940
We'll give you two some space.

389
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:07,300
Sure.

390
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:08,060
Thanks.

391
00:16:08,155 --> 00:16:10,100
Look at how eager you are.
There's plenty to eat.

392
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,133
We're still missing one.

393
00:16:11,730 --> 00:16:12,940
I'm back!

394
00:16:13,755 --> 00:16:15,130
Just in time. Help me take a look

395
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:16,370
at this draft.

396
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:18,980
Let me see.

397
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:19,770
Let's see it.

398
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:20,820
I just finished it.

399
00:16:22,010 --> 00:16:24,130
The Stepmother's Treasure Chest.

400
00:16:25,580 --> 00:16:27,130
Thirty years.

401
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:29,340
She raised her stepchildren
with everything she had.

402
00:16:29,580 --> 00:16:32,340
Yet all that waited for her
was a blank will,

403
00:16:32,340 --> 00:16:34,610
and the cold betrayal
of those she loved.

404
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,940
I want to remind everyone.

405
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:39,180
There is nothing wrong with being kind.

406
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:41,770
But don't let those who wear masks

407
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:43,460
exploit your kindness as a weakness.

408
00:16:43,650 --> 00:16:46,300
Maintain a baseline expectation
of human nature,

409
00:16:47,060 --> 00:16:49,370
and build your own
defense mechanisms early.

410
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:51,370
From your assets
to your mental health,

411
00:16:51,370 --> 00:16:53,420
insure yourself before it's too late.

412
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:54,820
Nicely written.

413
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:57,010
This is definitely going to go viral.

414
00:16:57,610 --> 00:16:58,650
You think so?

415
00:16:59,311 --> 00:17:00,730
Actually, I think the content

416
00:17:00,730 --> 00:17:02,300
is spot on.

417
00:17:03,130 --> 00:17:04,330
It's dramatic enough.

418
00:17:04,377 --> 00:17:06,666
(The Stepmother's Treasure Chest)
It's just that the title...

419
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:08,900
It doesn't quite...

420
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:10,180
hit you where it hurts.

421
00:17:10,620 --> 00:17:12,290
Yeah, I agree.

422
00:17:13,090 --> 00:17:14,660
The way you titled it

423
00:17:15,010 --> 00:17:16,570
sounds a bit like a Grimm's Fairy Tale.

424
00:17:16,570 --> 00:17:18,250
People might get the wrong idea.

425
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:22,660
I've been thinking about it for a while.

426
00:17:23,090 --> 00:17:24,290
I kept feeling like

427
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:27,900
it just wasn't good enough.

428
00:17:29,290 --> 00:17:30,050
The thing is,

429
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,940
everyone scrolls so fast these days.

430
00:17:32,290 --> 00:17:33,250
If the title

431
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,730
isn't eye-catching enough,

432
00:17:35,050 --> 00:17:36,770
no one is going to click and read it.

433
00:17:37,570 --> 00:17:39,620
So, what would be a better name?

434
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:44,810
How about...

435
00:17:45,810 --> 00:17:47,940
The Dragon-Slaying Brothers
and the Stepmother.

436
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:50,250
This isn't Water Margin.

437
00:17:52,090 --> 00:17:53,220
Then...

438
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:55,700
Maternal Love in a Treasure Chest.

439
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:57,810
That's basically what I already had.

440
00:17:58,010 --> 00:17:59,140
Pure Andersen's Fairy Tales.

441
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:02,980
Let's just be direct.

442
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:05,180
The Kind Stepmother
and the Biting Stepchildren.

443
00:18:05,180 --> 00:18:05,940
How's that?

444
00:18:05,940 --> 00:18:07,860
"The Kind Stepmother"...

445
00:18:07,860 --> 00:18:09,900
I think people want to see

446
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:12,090
a stepmother who doesn't bite

447
00:18:12,290 --> 00:18:14,090
but still finds a way to win.

448
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:16,380
So how do we title that?

449
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:21,530
Why not call it...

450
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:23,530
Kindness with Fangs.

451
00:18:24,090 --> 00:18:25,700
Right from the very beginning,

452
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,900
kindness should grow
sharp teeth and claws.

453
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:28,900
When faced with

454
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:31,010
those insatiable, greedy monsters,

455
00:18:31,380 --> 00:18:33,330
it can actually keep them in check.

456
00:18:33,422 --> 00:18:35,466
Only then can it protect
the heart of the matter,

457
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:37,620
and allow a kind person

458
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:39,090
to remain kind forever.

459
00:18:40,530 --> 00:18:41,660
Well said!

460
00:18:42,010 --> 00:18:45,220
Kindness isn't about being a doormat.

461
00:18:45,570 --> 00:18:48,570
(Kindness with Fangs)
Only kindness with edges is sustainable.

462
00:18:50,050 --> 00:18:50,980
I love that name.

463
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:54,220
I'm going to change now.

464
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:57,980
The wicked always meet their match.

465
00:18:58,730 --> 00:19:00,290
Great job. That was so satisfying!

466
00:19:00,620 --> 00:19:02,220
Hey, take it easy. People would think

467
00:19:02,220 --> 00:19:03,940
you were slamming a judge's gavel.

468
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:05,330
Like you're about to drag someone out

469
00:19:05,330 --> 00:19:06,490
and have them executed!

470
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:09,660
Isn't this even more painful
than an execution?

471
00:19:10,810 --> 00:19:12,660
One second, they think they've inherited

472
00:19:12,810 --> 00:19:13,620
millions in assets.

473
00:19:13,620 --> 00:19:15,660
Then, it turns into some baby teeth.

474
00:19:16,577 --> 00:19:17,730
And what do we call that?

475
00:19:17,730 --> 00:19:18,980
They had it coming.

476
00:19:20,911 --> 00:19:22,290
Seriously though, Shen Xiezhi...

477
00:19:22,940 --> 00:19:23,940
Impressive.

478
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:25,730
What was going through your head?

479
00:19:26,330 --> 00:19:27,570
You changed the approach,

480
00:19:27,570 --> 00:19:29,900
you changed the setting,
and the whole outcome shifted.

481
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,770
It was like the plan
was tailor-made for them.

482
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:35,140
Honestly, I was just
playing the supporting role.

483
00:19:35,420 --> 00:19:37,290
The first time Aixi and I
visited the client,

484
00:19:37,290 --> 00:19:38,980
we noticed that box and the teeth.

485
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:40,860
When Xianghui and I
were at the funeral,

486
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:43,700
I saw Ms. Qin holding that same box.

487
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,490
Then she gave me a look.

488
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:46,860
It just clicked for me.

489
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,420
I had to follow Ms. Qin's lead

490
00:19:48,620 --> 00:19:49,980
and play along with the act.

491
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:51,860
You're really something.

492
00:19:52,140 --> 00:19:54,770
Perfect teamwork
without even talking first.

493
00:19:55,050 --> 00:19:56,810
You truly have a gift, Shen.

494
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:00,380
Aixi! Aixi!

495
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:01,860
Did I hear that right?

496
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:04,090
How long has it been since

497
00:20:04,090 --> 00:20:05,770
Ms. Shu praised someone?

498
00:20:05,770 --> 00:20:07,980
Quick! Get a notebook
and write this down!

499
00:20:08,860 --> 00:20:09,570
Ms. Shu.

500
00:20:09,570 --> 00:20:11,050
If I write this in my notebook,

501
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:12,859
can it count as
a get-out-of-jail-free card?

502
00:20:12,860 --> 00:20:14,660
Am I usually that strict with you?

503
00:20:15,660 --> 00:20:17,810
No, I just have
very high standards for myself.

504
00:20:17,810 --> 00:20:19,330
I'm just nervous, that's all.

505
00:20:19,770 --> 00:20:22,050
Ms. Shu is a strict mentor at work.

506
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:24,180
She handles everything to the letter.

507
00:20:26,010 --> 00:20:27,380
From the moment you walked in,

508
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:28,250
I had a feeling

509
00:20:28,311 --> 00:20:30,530
today would turn into
a session to roast me, wouldn't it?

510
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:31,730
Ms. Shu...

511
00:20:33,490 --> 00:20:34,620
There's something I've wanted

512
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:36,010
to say to you for a long time.

513
00:20:36,010 --> 00:20:37,220
And I also want to apologize.

514
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:40,860
I was far too self-righteous before.

515
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,860
You kept emphasizing
the importance of mediation,

516
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:45,660
and I was always so resistant to it.

517
00:20:46,090 --> 00:20:47,490
I felt like it was just everyone

518
00:20:47,490 --> 00:20:49,220
abandoning their principles
to play nice.

519
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:52,010
Pushing the plaintiff
and defendant together,

520
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:53,290
seeing which side was softer

521
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:54,980
and more likely to cave.

522
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:57,420
Ignoring the rightful
interests of the victim

523
00:20:57,600 --> 00:20:59,220
just to settle for the sake of settling.

524
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:00,860
It felt inefficient and useless.

525
00:21:02,090 --> 00:21:02,770
Hey.

526
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:04,180
Self-reflection is one thing,

527
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:05,666
but does it have to be this deep?

528
00:21:06,050 --> 00:21:07,660
But I don't see it that way anymore.

529
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:12,330
After Mr. Yao's passing

530
00:21:13,090 --> 00:21:14,620
and Ms. Liu's case...

531
00:21:15,050 --> 00:21:16,900
I've seen the unique nature

532
00:21:17,180 --> 00:21:18,460
of the cases in our Family Court.

533
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,860
It's not just about
doing things by the book,

534
00:21:22,460 --> 00:21:25,290
or simply drawing a line
between right and wrong.

535
00:21:25,420 --> 00:21:27,620
It's about truly finding
a way out for the parties.

536
00:21:27,940 --> 00:21:29,180
Mediation is an art.

537
00:21:29,810 --> 00:21:31,940
And I've only just begun my journey.

538
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:33,620
Ms. Shu,

539
00:21:33,620 --> 00:21:34,940
I'll use this drink

540
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:36,620
instead of liquor to toast you.

541
00:21:37,220 --> 00:21:39,010
Thank you for all the patience

542
00:21:39,010 --> 00:21:40,460
and support you've shown me.

543
00:21:40,940 --> 00:21:42,010
Thanking me?

544
00:21:42,530 --> 00:21:44,730
He's not sounding like his usual self.

545
00:21:44,860 --> 00:21:45,490
It seems

546
00:21:45,490 --> 00:21:47,490
my hard work lately
hasn't gone to waste.

547
00:21:48,860 --> 00:21:49,730
Wait a minute.

548
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:50,570
Did you guys

549
00:21:50,570 --> 00:21:52,330
spike his drink or something?

550
00:21:53,090 --> 00:21:55,330
Let's send it
to the Forensics for testing.

551
00:21:55,530 --> 00:21:57,570
- No way.
- Absolutely not!

552
00:21:58,420 --> 00:22:00,250
Is this a flex?

553
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:01,460
Merely a flex?

554
00:22:01,460 --> 00:22:03,220
Or definitely a flex?

555
00:22:03,730 --> 00:22:04,730
Le,

556
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:06,250
you have to go easy on Ms. Shu.

557
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:08,330
Her apprentice is
officially flawless now.

558
00:22:08,330 --> 00:22:09,090
Right?

559
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:11,140
As a mentor,
she's bound to feel the pressure.

560
00:22:11,140 --> 00:22:12,660
The new wave is coming in strong.

561
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:15,860
It's normal for seniors
to feel a bit of a crisis.

562
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:17,660
Alright, Shen Xiezhi.

563
00:22:17,860 --> 00:22:19,180
Only you could pull that off.

564
00:22:21,010 --> 00:22:23,620
Is this work conference over?

565
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:24,420
If it is,

566
00:22:24,420 --> 00:22:26,400
then as the outsider,
I have a few things to say.

567
00:22:26,660 --> 00:22:27,420
Since

568
00:22:27,570 --> 00:22:29,420
tonight is a "soul-baring" night

569
00:22:29,420 --> 00:22:30,940
for our Shen,

570
00:22:30,940 --> 00:22:33,530
is there anything else you want to know

571
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:35,980
about his personal life?

572
00:22:36,330 --> 00:22:37,250
Ask away.

573
00:22:37,980 --> 00:22:39,980
As his best friend and childhood buddy,

574
00:22:39,980 --> 00:22:41,700
I'll tell you everything I know.

575
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:43,420
But it's a limited-time offer.

576
00:22:43,770 --> 00:22:44,620
Who knows when

577
00:22:44,620 --> 00:22:46,220
he'll crawl back into his shell?

578
00:22:46,530 --> 00:22:47,700
He'll probably come after me.

579
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,050
Ask now. Hurry.

580
00:22:49,050 --> 00:22:49,900
I've got one.

581
00:22:50,050 --> 00:22:50,660
Personally,

582
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:52,730
I'm very concerned
about Shen's private life.

583
00:22:53,220 --> 00:22:54,490
Tell me. After seeing all these

584
00:22:54,490 --> 00:22:56,220
messy families in court,

585
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:57,860
do you even have the guts to date?

586
00:22:58,460 --> 00:22:59,860
You're such a handsome young man.

587
00:22:59,860 --> 00:23:01,940
It'd be a shame to let you go to waste.

588
00:23:02,090 --> 00:23:02,900
Exactly!

589
00:23:03,180 --> 00:23:04,050
So, Judge Shen,

590
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:05,140
do you have a girlfriend?

591
00:23:05,140 --> 00:23:05,900
Do you have one?

592
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:07,140
Yeah, spill it! Do you?

593
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:09,570
Let's not be so shallow.

594
00:23:09,570 --> 00:23:11,250
I have a professional question.

595
00:23:12,666 --> 00:23:13,860
How did you pass the bar exam?

596
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:15,050
I've tried so many times.

597
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,700
You'd literally have to get a new brain.

598
00:23:19,533 --> 00:23:20,290
Come on, everyone.

599
00:23:20,290 --> 00:23:21,460
Let's have a toast!

600
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:22,530
Come on!

601
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:24,330
- To a great night!
- To a great night!

602
00:23:29,180 --> 00:23:30,420
Acting on behalf of my client,

603
00:23:30,420 --> 00:23:31,860
Mr. Feng Shengli,

604
00:23:32,290 --> 00:23:34,180
I am appearing in court
as his representative.

605
00:23:34,730 --> 00:23:36,140
Due to his illness,

606
00:23:36,140 --> 00:23:37,430
he is unable to attend in person.

607
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:38,460
That's impossible!

608
00:23:38,460 --> 00:23:39,620
(Authorized Representative. Plaintiff)
He'll say anything

609
00:23:39,620 --> 00:23:40,700
to avoid showing up.

610
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,460
(Authorized Representative. Defendant)
Do you really find it so hard to believe

611
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:43,530
a young man can get ill?

612
00:23:43,940 --> 00:23:46,010
Feng Shengli was born in the countryside

613
00:23:46,010 --> 00:23:48,180
with no family background
and no family support.

614
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:50,140
He could only rely on his meager income,

615
00:23:50,330 --> 00:23:51,940
waking up early and staying up late.

616
00:23:52,022 --> 00:23:53,860
It's either the 996
or the 007 work schedule.

617
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:55,490
Getting sick was only a matter of time.

618
00:23:55,620 --> 00:23:56,860
Other people could just quit,

619
00:23:57,090 --> 00:23:58,140
but he couldn't.

620
00:23:58,620 --> 00:23:59,660
Because what he carries

621
00:23:59,660 --> 00:24:01,460
is the hope of his entire birth family.

622
00:24:01,660 --> 00:24:02,980
So he had to push through.

623
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:04,460
He had to be there for overtime

624
00:24:04,460 --> 00:24:05,460
and business dinners.

625
00:24:05,460 --> 00:24:06,490
And the more he did that,

626
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:08,333
the more the company
dared to exploit him.

627
00:24:08,666 --> 00:24:09,810
In the first half of his life,

628
00:24:09,810 --> 00:24:11,044
he traded his health for money.

629
00:24:11,066 --> 00:24:11,810
In the second half,

630
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:13,244
he's trading that money for his life.

631
00:24:13,460 --> 00:24:15,330
Given my client's physical condition,

632
00:24:15,422 --> 00:24:17,010
he is not a match for a kidney donation.

633
00:24:17,220 --> 00:24:19,380
He cannot fulfill
the plaintiff's request.

634
00:24:21,180 --> 00:24:22,660
What is the plaintiff's position?

635
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,420
We don't need his kidney.

636
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:29,290
I'll donate mine to my father.

637
00:24:29,290 --> 00:24:30,980
He earns hundreds of thousands a year

638
00:24:31,155 --> 00:24:32,220
and has medical insurance.

639
00:24:32,333 --> 00:24:33,620
Covering medical expenses for two

640
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:34,700
should be easy for him.

641
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,090
Counsel for the defendant?

642
00:24:37,420 --> 00:24:38,570
Respectful Presiding Judge,

643
00:24:38,570 --> 00:24:40,090
my client is already ill.

644
00:24:40,090 --> 00:24:41,330
He was fired by his company.

645
00:24:41,622 --> 00:24:43,050
He no longer has social security.

646
00:24:43,220 --> 00:24:44,250
From this moment on,

647
00:24:44,530 --> 00:24:46,090
he has absolutely zero income.

648
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:48,090
This is impossible!

649
00:24:48,220 --> 00:24:49,010
Judge!

650
00:24:49,220 --> 00:24:50,180
She's lying!

651
00:24:50,288 --> 00:24:51,250
They're in this together!

652
00:24:51,250 --> 00:24:51,940
Silence.

653
00:24:51,940 --> 00:24:52,730
Presiding Judge,

654
00:24:52,980 --> 00:24:54,290
this is his termination notice.

655
00:24:55,490 --> 00:24:56,090
This...

656
00:24:56,250 --> 00:24:57,050
Thank you.

657
00:24:57,050 --> 00:24:57,770
How...

658
00:24:57,770 --> 00:24:58,420
How could he...

659
00:24:58,420 --> 00:24:59,290
This...

660
00:24:59,730 --> 00:25:01,180
Despite his own

661
00:25:01,180 --> 00:25:02,320
dire situation,

662
00:25:02,330 --> 00:25:04,290
he has already sold his house

663
00:25:04,290 --> 00:25:05,530
out of a sense of filial piety.

664
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,250
He will cover part of the medical costs.

665
00:25:07,250 --> 00:25:08,810
However, when he bought that house,

666
00:25:08,810 --> 00:25:10,010
he only paid the down payment.

667
00:25:10,380 --> 00:25:11,810
He has no more money to give.

668
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:13,533
He can only pay for actual expenses.

669
00:25:13,570 --> 00:25:14,660
Furthermore, since the father

670
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:16,420
was only examined in their hometown,

671
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:17,810
my client is concerned

672
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,860
about poor medical facilities
and misdiagnosis.

673
00:25:20,050 --> 00:25:21,620
He requests new examinations from

674
00:25:21,688 --> 00:25:22,933
a local Tertiary A hospital.

675
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:24,570
That's fine.

676
00:25:24,777 --> 00:25:26,155
I'll take him for the checkup.

677
00:25:26,288 --> 00:25:27,900
My dad isn't faking an illness.

678
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:29,810
Reimbursing actual expenses
is fine by us.

679
00:25:29,810 --> 00:25:31,660
We won't ask him for a single cent more.

680
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:34,330
To avoid any disputes over the spending,

681
00:25:34,620 --> 00:25:36,460
my client requests
that every single expense

682
00:25:36,460 --> 00:25:37,980
must be signed

683
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:39,533
and reviewed by a professional,

684
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,888
and then confirmed by the court.

685
00:25:41,010 --> 00:25:42,700
What review?

686
00:25:42,911 --> 00:25:44,977
To ensure the plaintiff's treatment
isn't delayed

687
00:25:45,050 --> 00:25:46,620
and to prevent accounting difficulties

688
00:25:46,620 --> 00:25:47,733
caused by long-term delays,

689
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,460
my client proposes that reviews

690
00:25:49,460 --> 00:25:51,511
should be held weekly,
as it is most reasonable.

691
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:53,570
The location will be
right here at this court.

692
00:25:54,377 --> 00:25:55,620
What's the meaning of this?

693
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:57,530
You think we're here to scam him?

694
00:25:57,810 --> 00:25:59,570
Tell him to get over here right now!

695
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,488
I'll face off with him
every single minute!

696
00:26:01,730 --> 00:26:03,010
You're his lawyer, right?

697
00:26:03,460 --> 00:26:04,900
I'll face off with you instead!

698
00:26:05,250 --> 00:26:06,530
Have you no shame?

699
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:09,220
Plaintiff, be quiet.

700
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:10,980
Do not insult the opposing counsel.

701
00:26:11,266 --> 00:26:12,644
Court is recessed for deliberation.

702
00:26:12,660 --> 00:26:14,740
(Hearing in progress)

703
00:26:19,810 --> 00:26:21,380
Kidney donation is a personal right.

704
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:23,220
We can't rule on that.

705
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:25,860
The current medical bills

706
00:26:25,860 --> 00:26:27,620
and diagnostic records are a mess.

707
00:26:28,044 --> 00:26:30,050
The old man refuses
to be hospitalized for tests.

708
00:26:30,222 --> 00:26:32,010
What are we supposed
to base a judgment on?

709
00:26:32,333 --> 00:26:33,822
Aside from a stay of proceedings,

710
00:26:34,180 --> 00:26:35,330
there's no other way.

711
00:26:35,330 --> 00:26:36,460
A stay is useless.

712
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:37,900
The old man only refuses

713
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:39,490
because he can't afford it.

714
00:26:39,620 --> 00:26:41,700
But the defendant won't
budge without proof.

715
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:44,090
It's a dead loop.

716
00:26:44,530 --> 00:26:45,730
What if we have Feng Shengli

717
00:26:45,730 --> 00:26:47,377
advance a portion of the medical fees?

718
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:50,090
If he's really sick, that's easy enough.

719
00:26:50,090 --> 00:26:51,810
But what if the uremia
was a misdiagnosis?

720
00:26:51,810 --> 00:26:53,050
In the end, would that money

721
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:54,090
be returned to the defendant?

722
00:26:54,090 --> 00:26:55,460
Wouldn't that be a happy ending?

723
00:26:55,733 --> 00:26:57,830
How much of a dispute
could there be over this sum?

724
00:26:58,180 --> 00:26:59,460
Feng Shengli is being difficult.

725
00:26:59,620 --> 00:27:00,530
His brother and sister

726
00:27:00,530 --> 00:27:02,180
could afford it with some hard effort.

727
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:05,010
What if the defendant insists
this is a scam to extort him?

728
00:27:06,010 --> 00:27:07,570
It seems his goal all along

729
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:09,490
has been to cut ties with the family,

730
00:27:10,250 --> 00:27:12,700
to shed his father,
his brother, and his sister,

731
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:14,066
who have been a burden to him.

732
00:27:14,090 --> 00:27:14,810
Exactly.

733
00:27:15,220 --> 00:27:16,090
This Feng Shengli case

734
00:27:16,090 --> 00:27:17,730
is getting a lot of attention online.

735
00:27:17,860 --> 00:27:19,220
If it ultimately turns out

736
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:20,810
the old man isn't actually sick,

737
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,490
public opinion will flip.

738
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:24,810
Feng Shengli will become the poor lamb

739
00:27:25,180 --> 00:27:26,620
being bled dry by his nuclear family.

740
00:27:26,940 --> 00:27:28,290
And we'll be seen as

741
00:27:28,570 --> 00:27:29,490
muddle-headed fools

742
00:27:29,490 --> 00:27:31,600
who aided a villain
and can't tell right from wrong.

743
00:27:31,770 --> 00:27:32,620
Are we supposed to

744
00:27:32,620 --> 00:27:34,010
gauge the media sentiment

745
00:27:34,010 --> 00:27:35,133
before we make a decision?

746
00:27:35,140 --> 00:27:36,730
No, no, that's not what I mean.

747
00:27:36,860 --> 00:27:37,810
When we rule on a case,

748
00:27:37,810 --> 00:27:40,290
the law is obviously
our benchmark, right?

749
00:27:40,290 --> 00:27:41,530
Everything is based on facts.

750
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:43,530
But what I'm trying to say is that

751
00:27:44,620 --> 00:27:45,460
public perception

752
00:27:45,460 --> 00:27:48,010
can't be ignored altogether.

753
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:49,010
Right?

754
00:27:49,010 --> 00:27:51,090
I just want to handle this
as thoroughly as possible.

755
00:27:51,090 --> 00:27:51,770
Otherwise,

756
00:27:51,770 --> 00:27:53,711
why would I move this case
to a collegial panel?

757
00:27:53,777 --> 00:27:54,940
I want to hear your opinions.

758
00:27:55,444 --> 00:27:56,730
I think the defendant should

759
00:27:56,730 --> 00:27:58,290
advance a portion of the medical fees.

760
00:27:58,620 --> 00:28:00,660
Let's ask the hospital
for the first phase of costs

761
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:02,220
and set a number first.

762
00:28:03,570 --> 00:28:04,620
What do you think?

763
00:28:06,010 --> 00:28:06,900
I agree.

764
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:10,570
The initial exam fees should
be under 100,000 yuan.

765
00:28:10,955 --> 00:28:12,977
His siblings are willing
to donate their kidneys.

766
00:28:13,050 --> 00:28:14,090
Public opinion

767
00:28:14,250 --> 00:28:15,570
shouldn't sway human nature.

768
00:28:16,330 --> 00:28:17,530
Given it's a chronic condition,

769
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:19,620
my concern is making a ruling

770
00:28:19,620 --> 00:28:20,660
without any test results.

771
00:28:20,660 --> 00:28:22,460
If his prediction comes true

772
00:28:22,620 --> 00:28:23,660
and it was a misdiagnosis,

773
00:28:23,980 --> 00:28:25,730
getting him to pay
for anything else later

774
00:28:25,730 --> 00:28:26,866
will be even more difficult.

775
00:28:26,911 --> 00:28:28,222
We should have a contingency plan.

776
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:30,420
Otherwise, given his attitude,

777
00:28:30,770 --> 00:28:31,140
he'd be

778
00:28:31,140 --> 00:28:32,810
a VIP of our Family Court.

779
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:34,700
If he's buying, we're selling.

780
00:28:34,844 --> 00:28:36,700
We'll even charge extra
for a Priority Pass.

781
00:28:36,777 --> 00:28:38,330
The father's treatment won't be delayed.

782
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:42,460
Fine.

783
00:28:43,050 --> 00:28:45,220
Since you both agree,

784
00:28:45,220 --> 00:28:47,250
I'll go with the majority.

785
00:28:47,490 --> 00:28:48,050
Alright.

786
00:28:48,220 --> 00:28:49,900
Two votes in favor, one against.

787
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:52,490
Motion passed. Let's resume the hearing.

788
00:28:52,980 --> 00:28:54,050
All rise.

789
00:28:57,530 --> 00:28:59,660
Please welcome
the Presiding Judge and the panel.

790
00:29:01,220 --> 00:29:02,490
The hearing will now resume.

791
00:29:03,220 --> 00:29:05,570
Do the plaintiff or defendant
have anything to add

792
00:29:05,570 --> 00:29:06,980
regarding their claims or evidence?

793
00:29:07,140 --> 00:29:07,900
Yes.

794
00:29:08,290 --> 00:29:10,250
Our families all live out of town.

795
00:29:11,490 --> 00:29:13,530
We have jobs, wives,
and children to care for,

796
00:29:13,900 --> 00:29:15,460
plus a sick father to look after.

797
00:29:15,660 --> 00:29:17,330
It's impossible for us to come to court

798
00:29:17,530 --> 00:29:19,420
every single week to bicker with him.

799
00:29:19,810 --> 00:29:20,900
I've done the math.

800
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:21,900
Between the transplant

801
00:29:22,180 --> 00:29:24,460
and the subsequent recovery care,

802
00:29:24,660 --> 00:29:26,010
it'll be roughly 500,000 yuan.

803
00:29:26,420 --> 00:29:28,010
We don't need him to cover all of it.

804
00:29:28,290 --> 00:29:29,770
If he pays 250,000 yuan,

805
00:29:29,770 --> 00:29:31,380
we'll consider the matter settled.

806
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:33,420
We won't meet ever again.

807
00:29:33,770 --> 00:29:34,660
As for

808
00:29:35,330 --> 00:29:37,490
any further treatments down the road,

809
00:29:37,730 --> 00:29:38,530
or

810
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:40,620
if complications or rejection occur,

811
00:29:40,810 --> 00:29:41,900
my sister and I

812
00:29:42,860 --> 00:29:44,330
will scrape together whatever we can.

813
00:29:44,810 --> 00:29:45,860
If it's not enough,

814
00:29:47,810 --> 00:29:49,330
then that's just my father's fate.

815
00:29:50,010 --> 00:29:51,180
He chose to spend his life

816
00:29:51,460 --> 00:29:53,490
raising such a successful son.

817
00:29:54,810 --> 00:29:55,700
This is

818
00:29:56,530 --> 00:29:57,420
his blame to bear.

819
00:30:00,380 --> 00:30:02,220
Given the change
in the plaintiff's demands,

820
00:30:02,220 --> 00:30:03,244
Counsel for the Defendant,

821
00:30:03,311 --> 00:30:05,180
do you need
to consult with your client?

822
00:30:05,570 --> 00:30:07,770
I have already communicated
with my client.

823
00:30:07,980 --> 00:30:09,090
Given the circumstances,

824
00:30:09,810 --> 00:30:12,050
my client is willing
to pay 350,000 yuan.

825
00:30:18,220 --> 00:30:20,380
On the condition that they sign

826
00:30:20,660 --> 00:30:22,250
a 100,000 IOU in front of the judge.

827
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:24,460
What?

828
00:30:30,940 --> 00:30:31,844
(Hearing in progress)

829
00:30:37,010 --> 00:30:39,380
Mr. Feng,
please reply to my message soon.

830
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,090
I've settled this matter for you.

831
00:30:41,250 --> 00:30:43,010
Please take care of the final payment.

832
00:30:43,380 --> 00:30:45,090
To be honest, I don't quite understand.

833
00:30:45,420 --> 00:30:47,220
You sold your house

834
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,533
to come up with that 350,000 yuan.

835
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:50,280
Why bother bearing the bad reputation?

836
00:30:52,660 --> 00:30:54,330
Fortunately, we had the evidence,

837
00:30:54,330 --> 00:30:56,220
and the public backlash has subsided.

838
00:30:56,420 --> 00:30:58,290
The family has also agreed to settle.

839
00:30:58,530 --> 00:30:59,660
In terms of procedure,

840
00:30:59,810 --> 00:31:01,770
our Family Court judges

841
00:31:01,770 --> 00:31:02,810
didn't make any mistakes.

842
00:31:03,250 --> 00:31:05,530
But when it comes to social nuances

843
00:31:05,730 --> 00:31:06,940
and interpersonal methods,

844
00:31:06,940 --> 00:31:08,810
Xiezhi still needs more honing from you.

845
00:31:09,940 --> 00:31:10,660
Come in.

846
00:31:11,420 --> 00:31:12,330
Ms. Shu.

847
00:31:13,420 --> 00:31:14,220
Mr. He is here too.

848
00:31:14,220 --> 00:31:15,140
Xiezhi.

849
00:31:15,730 --> 00:31:17,530
You two carry on. I'll head out.

850
00:31:17,660 --> 00:31:19,530
We're already done. Have a seat.

851
00:31:20,050 --> 00:31:21,420
With Mr. He here,

852
00:31:21,420 --> 00:31:22,660
he can give you some advice.

853
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:23,860
Come on, sit down.

854
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:25,810
Alright.

855
00:31:30,911 --> 00:31:32,090
So, what's on your mind?

856
00:31:33,220 --> 00:31:34,940
I want to talk
about Feng Shengli's case.

857
00:31:35,380 --> 00:31:36,180
Go ahead.

858
00:31:37,620 --> 00:31:39,220
From a mediation perspective,

859
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:40,980
the siblings want money,

860
00:31:41,022 --> 00:31:42,620
and Feng Shengli is willing to pay.

861
00:31:42,860 --> 00:31:43,770
That's a good start.

862
00:31:44,050 --> 00:31:45,090
And since Feng Shengli

863
00:31:45,090 --> 00:31:46,530
offered an extra 100,000 yuan,

864
00:31:46,530 --> 00:31:47,490
it's even better.

865
00:31:47,700 --> 00:31:50,220
It looks like a win-win for everyone.

866
00:31:50,810 --> 00:31:53,420
But because of the IOU
he's demanding they sign,

867
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:54,860
I don't feel like

868
00:31:54,860 --> 00:31:56,140
this case has been resolved.

869
00:31:56,810 --> 00:31:58,490
Feng Shengli's goal all along

870
00:31:58,490 --> 00:32:00,460
has been to cut ties with his family.

871
00:32:00,980 --> 00:32:02,420
This 100-grand IOU

872
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,090
is likely to become the very tether

873
00:32:04,090 --> 00:32:05,822
that keeps them connected in the future.

874
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:08,090
If Feng Shengli ever
wants that money back,

875
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:10,180
he'll have to seek out his siblings.

876
00:32:10,490 --> 00:32:12,770
And if they refuse to pay him back,

877
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:15,810
their relationship will just be
at a stalemate again.

878
00:32:20,290 --> 00:32:22,140
Have you considered another possibility?

879
00:32:22,570 --> 00:32:23,330
What if he

880
00:32:23,330 --> 00:32:25,180
never intended to get that money back?

881
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:26,810
From the very start,

882
00:32:26,810 --> 00:32:29,010
Feng Shengli's goal has never changed.

883
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:31,770
He wants to sever ties with them.

884
00:32:31,980 --> 00:32:32,660
Right.

885
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,460
But legally,

886
00:32:34,460 --> 00:32:36,290
that's not a request
the court can support.

887
00:32:37,250 --> 00:32:39,620
So Feng Shengli is using that money

888
00:32:40,660 --> 00:32:42,570
to buy his siblings' silence.

889
00:32:42,980 --> 00:32:44,490
If they can't pay him back,

890
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:46,090
they won't dare contact him.

891
00:32:48,290 --> 00:32:50,050
On the surface, it's a happy ending.

892
00:32:50,330 --> 00:32:53,010
But it's just a clever trick
that leaves endless trouble.

893
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:56,250
So, how do you want to rule?

894
00:32:56,250 --> 00:32:57,330
This 100,000 yuan

895
00:32:57,530 --> 00:32:59,290
could very well be the death sentence

896
00:32:59,290 --> 00:33:00,490
for their family bond.

897
00:33:01,220 --> 00:33:02,010
Ms. Shu,

898
00:33:02,288 --> 00:33:04,133
I want to see Feng Shengli
one more time.

899
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:04,770
Fine.

900
00:33:04,900 --> 00:33:06,530
I'll handle things with Mr. Ying.

901
00:33:06,530 --> 00:33:07,570
You go ahead and contact him.

902
00:33:07,570 --> 00:33:08,290
Okay.

903
00:33:08,810 --> 00:33:10,730
Thank you for the guidance,
Ms. Shu and Mr. He.

904
00:33:11,140 --> 00:33:11,810
Xiezhi.

905
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:13,220
If you have any issues,

906
00:33:13,220 --> 00:33:14,770
come straight to my office.

907
00:33:15,860 --> 00:33:17,290
I didn't want to bother you.

908
00:33:17,940 --> 00:33:19,730
At the age your parents and I are at,

909
00:33:19,940 --> 00:33:21,220
we're not afraid of any bother.

910
00:33:21,220 --> 00:33:22,660
We're afraid you won't.

911
00:33:23,860 --> 00:33:24,530
I understand.

912
00:33:25,810 --> 00:33:26,660
I'll get back to work.

913
00:33:26,660 --> 00:33:28,090
Alright. Go on.

914
00:33:49,530 --> 00:33:49,940
Mom.

915
00:33:49,940 --> 00:33:51,620
Son?
What are you doing home so suddenly?

916
00:33:55,290 --> 00:33:56,460
I got off work early today.

917
00:33:56,460 --> 00:33:57,730
I came to see Grandpa.

918
00:33:57,730 --> 00:33:59,940
He's inside with your father. Go on.

919
00:34:02,810 --> 00:34:03,620
What's wrong?

920
00:34:04,050 --> 00:34:05,140
Are you mad at your dad?

921
00:34:05,860 --> 00:34:07,010
I wouldn't dare.

922
00:34:07,530 --> 00:34:09,610
I'm just afraid
I'll say the wrong thing again

923
00:34:09,860 --> 00:34:10,940
and set him off.

924
00:34:11,130 --> 00:34:12,460
He'll just call me a disgrace

925
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:13,533
who can't handle hardship

926
00:34:13,570 --> 00:34:14,490
and is a burden to him.

927
00:34:14,650 --> 00:34:16,490
How can you think that of your father?

928
00:34:16,490 --> 00:34:19,010
He's just not good
at expressing his feelings.

929
00:34:19,210 --> 00:34:20,940
We've been married all these years,

930
00:34:21,130 --> 00:34:23,490
and he hasn't said
a single romantic thing to me.

931
00:34:23,490 --> 00:34:24,530
Who knows?

932
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:26,690
Maybe he's just heartless.

933
00:34:27,570 --> 00:34:29,380
I know you two better than anyone.

934
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:31,460
Every bit of your father's temperament

935
00:34:31,460 --> 00:34:32,866
was passed straight down to you.

936
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:34,740
Tell me, are you heartless too?

937
00:34:35,050 --> 00:34:36,980
You've been
in the Family Court long enough.

938
00:34:36,980 --> 00:34:37,980
After all those cases,

939
00:34:38,170 --> 00:34:40,420
don't you understand
your father's intentions?

940
00:34:41,010 --> 00:34:41,740
Alright.

941
00:34:41,980 --> 00:34:42,740
Go on.

942
00:34:43,490 --> 00:34:44,530
Be good to your father.

943
00:34:44,940 --> 00:34:45,900
I know, I know.

944
00:34:52,010 --> 00:34:53,170
Grandpa? What are you doing?

945
00:34:55,130 --> 00:34:55,820
Zhi!

946
00:34:56,010 --> 00:34:56,980
You're back.

947
00:34:57,222 --> 00:34:59,010
Look at this.
We have way too many books.

948
00:34:59,010 --> 00:35:00,090
I'm sorting through them.

949
00:35:00,460 --> 00:35:02,010
Picking some out to give away.

950
00:35:03,610 --> 00:35:04,690
Did you see your father?

951
00:35:08,130 --> 00:35:09,380
You're getting rid of these?

952
00:35:10,010 --> 00:35:11,420
But these are your treasures.

953
00:35:11,420 --> 00:35:13,380
I've memorized most of them by now.

954
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:15,010
There's no need to keep them around.

955
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:15,820
Grandpa,

956
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:17,740
if you don't have space for them,

957
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:18,900
just put them in my room.

958
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:20,210
No one's staying there anyway.

959
00:35:20,333 --> 00:35:21,650
It's a waste to give them away.

960
00:35:21,650 --> 00:35:22,780
No, that won't do.

961
00:35:23,570 --> 00:35:24,300
In any case,

962
00:35:24,300 --> 00:35:26,170
that room is staying
exactly as it is for you.

963
00:35:26,610 --> 00:35:28,380
This will always be your home.

964
00:35:30,380 --> 00:35:31,210
Dad.

965
00:35:31,380 --> 00:35:33,530
I found a few more
in the upstairs study.

966
00:35:35,980 --> 00:35:36,780
Xiezhi.

967
00:35:37,090 --> 00:35:38,050
You're home.

968
00:35:39,490 --> 00:35:40,300
Dad.

969
00:35:41,570 --> 00:35:43,860
Come, look at these
other books I found.

970
00:35:50,460 --> 00:35:51,010
Xiezhi,

971
00:35:51,010 --> 00:35:52,460
it's been so long since you visited.

972
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:54,530
Are you seeing someone?

973
00:35:55,690 --> 00:35:57,130
The court has been buried in work.

974
00:35:57,130 --> 00:35:59,170
There's no time for dating, Grandpa.

975
00:36:00,050 --> 00:36:01,460
Well, I was just hoping

976
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:03,650
to have a grandson soon.

977
00:36:06,380 --> 00:36:07,170
Jingsheng.

978
00:36:07,690 --> 00:36:10,130
Have you found anyone suitable
at your workplace?

979
00:36:11,980 --> 00:36:12,650
No.

980
00:36:12,780 --> 00:36:14,170
You know, as a father,

981
00:36:14,170 --> 00:36:15,555
how can you be so indifferent

982
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:16,780
to your son's future marriage?

983
00:36:17,490 --> 00:36:19,780
Grandpa, stop teasing me.

984
00:36:19,780 --> 00:36:21,900
With the reputation
my dad has at school,

985
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:24,130
what girl would dare
to be his daughter-in-law?

986
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:28,340
Xiezhi.

987
00:36:28,530 --> 00:36:29,900
Have you read this book?

988
00:36:30,210 --> 00:36:31,780
I've only read the English version.

989
00:36:32,050 --> 00:36:33,090
My students...

990
00:36:33,780 --> 00:36:34,690
Well, they say

991
00:36:34,690 --> 00:36:36,490
the Chinese translation
of certain chapters

992
00:36:36,490 --> 00:36:37,300
is a bit clunky.

993
00:36:40,820 --> 00:36:41,460
I've read it.

994
00:36:42,340 --> 00:36:43,610
Go on. Let's hear your thoughts.

995
00:36:46,740 --> 00:36:48,530
I used to think that being a judge

996
00:36:48,530 --> 00:36:50,490
required absolute, cold objectivity.

997
00:36:50,490 --> 00:36:52,420
That we couldn't be emotional
like normal people.

998
00:36:52,740 --> 00:36:54,420
But this book presents a different view.

999
00:36:54,610 --> 00:36:55,740
Judges are human, too.

1000
00:36:56,460 --> 00:36:57,490
And as humans,

1001
00:36:57,900 --> 00:36:59,820
we can't entirely
escape external factors

1002
00:36:59,820 --> 00:37:01,740
influencing our judicial actions.

1003
00:37:02,133 --> 00:37:03,610
However, within effective constraints,

1004
00:37:03,780 --> 00:37:05,170
a judge's proactive intervention

1005
00:37:05,740 --> 00:37:07,860
can still play a critical role.

1006
00:37:09,130 --> 00:37:09,980
So,

1007
00:37:10,210 --> 00:37:12,570
your experience in the Family Court

1008
00:37:13,460 --> 00:37:14,860
hasn't been a waste of time.

1009
00:37:18,690 --> 00:37:19,610
It hasn't.

1010
00:37:21,490 --> 00:37:22,460
That's good.

1011
00:37:36,377 --> 00:37:37,860
(Qingcheng District People's Court)

1012
00:37:41,888 --> 00:37:43,650
Feng Shengli lives out that way, right?

1013
00:37:44,044 --> 00:37:46,266
(Road Construction)
Great hiding spot. That place is remote.

1014
00:37:46,380 --> 00:37:48,222
He was a programmer
at a big tech company.

1015
00:37:48,333 --> 00:37:50,010
Now he's lost his job
and sold his house.

1016
00:37:50,010 --> 00:37:51,170
To hide from his family,

1017
00:37:51,170 --> 00:37:52,422
he's moved to the outskirts.

1018
00:37:52,533 --> 00:37:53,755
It's so unusual.

1019
00:37:53,844 --> 00:37:56,210
I'm heading to Qiaoxi Village
to deliver a hearing notice.

1020
00:37:56,210 --> 00:37:57,210
It's right near there.

1021
00:37:57,210 --> 00:37:58,170
I'll go take a look.

1022
00:37:58,820 --> 00:37:59,610
I'm coming with you.

1023
00:37:59,610 --> 00:38:00,777
Is that really necessary?

1024
00:38:00,860 --> 00:38:01,420
We're only

1025
00:38:01,420 --> 00:38:02,900
telling him to attend the mediation.

1026
00:38:03,050 --> 00:38:04,130
The notice isn't the point.

1027
00:38:04,130 --> 00:38:06,340
His attitude
toward the mediation is what matters.

1028
00:38:06,780 --> 00:38:08,130
I'd better go with you.

1029
00:38:08,260 --> 00:38:09,130
Alright.

1030
00:38:10,980 --> 00:38:14,260
(Qingcheng District People's Court,
Tianhai City)

1031
00:38:25,460 --> 00:38:27,620
(Feng Shengli)

1032
00:38:30,210 --> 00:38:31,170
(That Feng Shengli...)

1033
00:38:31,355 --> 00:38:33,210
(Why hasn't he answered
his phone for days?)

1034
00:38:33,333 --> 00:38:34,870
(He isn't replying to messages either.)

1035
00:38:34,980 --> 00:38:35,980
(What's going on?)

1036
00:38:36,977 --> 00:38:39,444
(North Changjiang Road)
(Is he dodging the final payment?)

1037
00:38:40,530 --> 00:38:42,820
(Did something happen to him?)

1038
00:38:44,490 --> 00:38:45,610
(I'd better go check.)

1039
00:38:54,820 --> 00:38:55,780
Are you okay?

1040
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:57,400
These mountain roads
are a nightmare.

1041
00:38:57,466 --> 00:38:58,933
I should have borrowed an off-roader.

1042
00:39:00,300 --> 00:39:02,420
On this road,
it doesn't matter what you drive.

1043
00:39:03,860 --> 00:39:04,780
Take it slow.

1044
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:05,820
Will do.

1045
00:39:27,060 --> 00:39:28,700
(45 minutes. 3.8 km)

1046
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:29,540
(Sangxia Tea Garden)

1047
00:39:29,644 --> 00:39:32,000
(Sangxia Tea Garden)
(How much longer is this going to take?)

1048
00:39:47,010 --> 00:39:48,940
How's Fei? Who's watching her?

1049
00:39:49,355 --> 00:39:50,733
Much better. Her fever broke.

1050
00:39:50,777 --> 00:39:51,940
She still has a bit of a cough.

1051
00:39:51,940 --> 00:39:53,288
I dropped her off with her dad.

1052
00:39:54,130 --> 00:39:55,170
Did you hear?

1053
00:39:55,300 --> 00:39:56,090
What?

1054
00:39:57,111 --> 00:39:58,888
Tong was discharged from the hospital.

1055
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:04,590
My brother-in-law was doing
so well in the Criminal Division.

1056
00:40:04,650 --> 00:40:06,460
Why did he quit
to open a mutton soup shop?

1057
00:40:07,170 --> 00:40:08,570
It's a long story.

1058
00:40:08,820 --> 00:40:10,050
It was all because of Tong.

1059
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:11,980
Tong was Ms. Shu's neighbor.

1060
00:40:11,980 --> 00:40:14,490
Ms. Shu and her husband
were always so busy with work

1061
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,555
that they often
couldn't look after their child.

1062
00:40:16,570 --> 00:40:18,570
So Tong's mom would
pick Fei up to watch her.

1063
00:40:19,170 --> 00:40:21,130
Tong would play with Fei every day.

1064
00:40:21,260 --> 00:40:23,010
They were closer than real sisters.

1065
00:40:23,650 --> 00:40:25,260
About a year ago,

1066
00:40:26,210 --> 00:40:27,740
Tong's mom was busy one day,

1067
00:40:28,130 --> 00:40:30,490
so she asked Mr. Lian
to pick Tong up instead.

1068
00:40:30,780 --> 00:40:32,340
But then he got a call from the court,

1069
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:33,900
telling him he had to come back in.

1070
00:40:33,900 --> 00:40:35,740
Since they were only
a few minutes from home,

1071
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:38,311
Mr. Lian told Tong
to get out at the alley entrance

1072
00:40:38,333 --> 00:40:39,244
and walk home.

1073
00:40:39,740 --> 00:40:41,490
Who would have thought that

1074
00:40:41,822 --> 00:40:43,380
something bad would happen to her?

1075
00:40:43,740 --> 00:40:45,010
She was raped.

1076
00:40:45,490 --> 00:40:47,260
It was pitch black in that alley.

1077
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:49,010
Tong couldn't see anything clearly,

1078
00:40:49,010 --> 00:40:51,133
but she insisted it was
Mr. Lian who did it.

1079
00:40:51,244 --> 00:40:52,490
The police investigation found

1080
00:40:52,490 --> 00:40:53,940
that Mr. Lian had an alibi.

1081
00:40:54,260 --> 00:40:55,610
But Tong refused to believe it.

1082
00:40:55,780 --> 00:40:57,466
She insisted they were all in on it too.

1083
00:40:57,530 --> 00:40:59,090
The doctors said that Tong

1084
00:40:59,090 --> 00:41:00,610
was suffering from PTSD.

1085
00:41:00,610 --> 00:41:01,530
And if it got any worse,

1086
00:41:01,530 --> 00:41:02,980
she might develop violent tendencies.

1087
00:41:02,980 --> 00:41:04,130
Tong's mom had no choice

1088
00:41:04,130 --> 00:41:05,570
but to send her to a care facility.

1089
00:41:05,780 --> 00:41:08,010
But Fei was deeply
traumatized by the whole ordeal.

1090
00:41:08,420 --> 00:41:09,650
Mr. Lian realized

1091
00:41:09,650 --> 00:41:11,377
he'd spent
all those years focusing on work

1092
00:41:11,390 --> 00:41:12,730
and having neglected his daughter.

1093
00:41:12,980 --> 00:41:14,530
So he chose to resign

1094
00:41:15,130 --> 00:41:17,780
and opened a mutton soup shop
near her school.

1095
00:41:18,490 --> 00:41:19,610
For over a year,

1096
00:41:19,740 --> 00:41:22,050
he watched over her day and night.

1097
00:41:22,511 --> 00:41:24,050
Fei is finally doing much better now.

1098
00:41:24,050 --> 00:41:25,820
A parent's love really knows no bounds.

1099
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:31,170
Wait, isn't it next week?

1100
00:41:38,940 --> 00:41:42,220
(Fei. Lian's Mutton Soup Shop)

1101
00:41:42,380 --> 00:41:44,340
This GPS location is totally unclear.

1102
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:45,610
Xianghui,

1103
00:41:45,820 --> 00:41:47,090
just pull over up ahead.

1104
00:41:47,380 --> 00:41:48,610
Let's split up and search.

1105
00:41:54,133 --> 00:41:56,200
(Sangxia Tea Garden)
Call if you find anything first.

1106
00:41:56,300 --> 00:41:57,900
Maybe I should search
through the place?

1107
00:41:57,900 --> 00:41:59,690
No, you guys stick to the road.
Look closely.

1108
00:42:00,130 --> 00:42:01,090
See you later.

1109
00:42:20,210 --> 00:42:20,980
Qin Rui?

1110
00:42:23,090 --> 00:42:24,050
Judge Shen.

1111
00:42:24,940 --> 00:42:25,900
What are you doing here?

1112
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:28,380
What are you doing here?

1113
00:42:28,380 --> 00:42:29,610
I came to find Feng Shengli.

1114
00:42:31,050 --> 00:42:31,900
You too?

1115
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,340
Yeah. I'm looking for him as well.

1116
00:42:34,380 --> 00:42:35,490
Do you know where he lives?

1117
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:37,460
I have an address for him.

1118
00:42:38,420 --> 00:42:40,130
Why are you looking for him?

1119
00:42:40,130 --> 00:42:41,940
The court wants to organize
another mediation.

1120
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:43,380
But he's gone missing.

1121
00:42:43,380 --> 00:42:44,860
I thought this case was closed?

1122
00:42:45,010 --> 00:42:45,955
Why another mediation?

1123
00:42:46,022 --> 00:42:47,340
The defendant wasn't even present,

1124
00:42:47,530 --> 00:42:48,130
yet we

1125
00:42:48,130 --> 00:42:50,170
certified a father
and son disowning each other.

1126
00:42:50,340 --> 00:42:51,460
Is that reasonable?

1127
00:42:53,900 --> 00:42:55,460
Personally, of course I hope

1128
00:42:55,460 --> 00:42:56,940
their family can reconcile.

1129
00:42:57,340 --> 00:42:58,980
But I can't
get in touch with him either.

1130
00:42:58,980 --> 00:43:00,130
Then what are your client's

1131
00:43:00,130 --> 00:43:00,980
current thoughts?

1132
00:43:01,210 --> 00:43:02,650
Is he avoiding the mediation

1133
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:03,900
and the payment?

1134
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1135
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1136
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1137
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1138
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1139
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1140
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1141
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1142
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1143
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1144
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1145
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1146
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1147
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1148
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1149
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1150
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1151
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1152
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1153
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1154
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1155
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1156
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1157
